The calls for Arsene Wenger to leave his post as Arsenal manager strengthened on Saturday, with travelling supporters at The Hawthorns for their team's game against West Brom unravelling a banner demanding his immediate departure.

Fans held up a sign that read 'Arsene, thanks for the memories but it's time to say goodbye' during Arsenal's 1-0 win at West Brom.

Another supporter protested by holding a sign saying 'Enough is enough, Wenger out.'

