Arsenal have begun the season in an unconvincing manner, and a 2-1 home defeat last weekend to Manchester United has left many fans questioning whether Arsenal can ever again reach the heights that they once hit under Wenger's guidance.

But the Frenchman has overseen two victories since that loss.

Before the West Brom win, Arsenal beat Borussia Dortmund 2-0 in the Champions League on Wednesday to secure a place in the last 16 of Europe's elite club competition.

 

 

